F3Q Missed and Lowered; FY26 CommentsSolid; Lowering PT to 35

COO reported F3Q revs of $1,060 MM,+5.7%,+3% xfx and 2% org, below cons of $1,064 MM (+6.1%) as both CVI and CSI were softer. CVI organic growth of 2% was below cons of 5.8%. F4Q guide came in below cons as well at 2-4% organic for both CVI and CSI. For FY26, COO remains optimistic that the CL market will still grow in the MSD range and expects to take share with increasing MyDay supply. We update our model, reiterate Buy and lower PT to $85.

**F3Q Missed:** COO reported F3Q25 revs of $1,060 MM,+5.7% reported,+3% xfx and 2% organic,below cons of $1,064 MM (+6.1% reported). CVI generated $718 MM,+6.3% reported,+2% xfx and organic, below cons. $721 MM (+6.7% reported,+5.8% organic). CSI revs of $341.9 MM was +4.5% reported, +4% xfx, and +2% organic, vs cons of $342 MM (+4.5% reported) as Fertility grew 3%organic, and Paragard was -10%, as expected.

**CVI +2% Organic**: Growth was driven by 6% Toric and MF, partially offset by -1% Sphere. MyDay grew DD driven by more capacity going online. CVI has 30+ new MyDay private label contracts,almost 50% increase in fitting sets yoy. In FY25, COO is expected to do ~$1 B in daily SiHy revs, with ~$600 MM MyDay and ~$400 MM clariti. 7% daily SiHy growth from MyDay (DD) and Clariti, while FRPs grew 2% from Biofinity and Avaira. clariti had a challenging quarter as customers focused on MyDay, which is expected to persist for the next couple of quarters.

**MiSight grew 23% to ~$30 MM with another record setting EMEA.** Americas was mixed but back to school promotions are seeing positive fitting trends. Japan received reg approval. MyDay MiSight will be launching across EMEA and in parts of APAC in F1H26. COO continues to expect $100+MM in revs or 25%+ yoy growth. COO continues to expect the CL market to grow MSD with solid consumption trends, steady shift towards daily SiHys and interest in premium Torics and MFs. COO expects trade ups to continue while pricing and wearer growth to be less impactful.

**CSI +2% Organic**: Fertility grew 3% organic, while Ofc & Surgical was +1% organic as the Fertility pressures persisted and Paragard came in at -10%, as expected. The Fertility market improved slightly, esp for genomics and consumables. Year of the Snake is behind them and COO saw small improvements in APAC, but cycle remains soft. F4Q faces a tough 13% comp, but growth should improve from there. LT 800 remains positive on the Fertility market.

**F4Q25 Guide Below Cons; Early FY26 Comments Encouraging:** Given what COO saw in the 1H market, and factoring in some level of conservatism, COO provided F4Q guidance of 2-4% organic for both CVI and CSI. Product launches include MyDay Energys in EU in early FY26, MyDay MFs into several major APAC markets soon, and more supply in other geographies, and MyDay Toric paraqueer expansions.
We are updating revs and EPS given the F3Q miss and updated FY guide. We are lowering PT to 35% from $105, based on ~19x FY26 EPS of $4.42.
Equity ResearchAugust 28,2025

**Young Li* | Equity Analyst**

- Buy thesis predicated on: Material increases in capex to ramp up daily SiHys supply coming online in F2H24/2025.  
- Strong CL market driven by daily SiHys trade-ups.  
- Pricing remaining stable/strong at \(2 - 3\%\) .  
- Continued share taking from JNJ.  
- Increased supply enables COO to launch more torics and multifocals as well as expand more geographically such as in APAC.  
- Consumer health remaining resilient; with COO's private label business a competitive advantage and differentiation in case of a recession.  
- Margin expansion xfx and on reported basis as fx reverses.  
- Stable CSI business driven by strong Fertility and M&A apptics.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

- 8CVI growth accelerates with more supply coming online.  
- New patient starts within Orthok portfolio track in line with forecasts.  
- Trade-ups to daily SiHy continue to progress, driven by better outcomes and convenience.  
- Continued share gains from JNJ.  
- Paragard continues to take price.  
- MiSight patient volumes holding steady with new patient starts growing.  
- Tax rate remains below industry average.
- Base case PT: \(85\) using \(\sim 19x\) our FY2026 EPS.

- CVI growth of HSD/LDD and track ahead of market growth.  
- Continued momentum ahead of contact lens markets.  
- Overall trade ups return to pre-covid levels including trade-up to premium SiHy lenses (MyDay).  
- Share gains from CL competitors.  
- Paragard competitive overhang removal and continued pricing.  
- MiSight takes share and new patient starts sees robust growth, Orthok portfolio sees sizable growth y/y.  
- Tax rate remains below industry average.  
- Bull case PT: \(100\) using \(\sim 21x\) our bull case FY2026 EPS.

- CVI growth tracks below contact lens market growth on combo share loss and price cuts.  
- clariti/MyDay loss share to competitive launches.  
- Paragard share impacted by competitor.  
- MiSight uptake is slow, driven by recession and competitive products.  
- Tax policy changes result in a higher effective rate.  
- Competitive entry by Amazon into contact lens space.  
- Bear Case PT: \(60\) using \(\sim 15x\) our bear case FY2026 EPS.

Top Material Issue(s): Product Design & Lifecycle Mgmt: COO partnered with Plastic Bank to create a net plastic- natural contact lens and has purchased credits from Plastic Bank to offset 1 day contact lenses in the DS and Europe. Employee Engagement, Diversity & Inclusion: Cooper is investing \(\sim\) 2 MM over a 3- year period to develop digital learning solutions to help employees develop key skills to advance their careers within Cooper. Human Rights & Community Relations: COO has partnered with the Special Olympics to provide high- quality vision eyewear as well as ocular health screenings and education to athletes in Kenya and the US.
Company Targets: Expand the Plastic Bank program to 27 countries WW.

Qs for mgmt: How has your employee retention rate and internal promotion rate changed since implementing the digital learning initiative? Does the Plastic Bank initiative give you an advantage compared to other competitors in the space? Link to ESG MedTech Framework

- MiSight clinical data and continued US growth  
- Daily SiHy trade ups  
- Higher global net pricing  
- Increasing supply in F25  
- Introduction of new products  
- Expanding APAC geography  
- Paragard generic competition overhang removal  
- SightGlass 2H25 FDA approval  
- CSI M&A

**F4Q25 Guide Below Cons; Early FY26 Comments Encouraging:** Given what COO saw in the 1H market, and factoring in some level of conservatism, COO provided F4Q guidance of 2-4% organic for both CVI and CSI. Product launches include My Energy in EU in early FY26, MyDay MFs into several major APAC markets soon, and more in other geographies, and MyDay Toric parameter expansions.

Cooper CompaniesCooper Companies is a diversified medical device group that develops, manufactures and markets products for two distinct markets: vision care (CooperVision CVI, 2/3 of revenue) and women's health (CooperSurgical CSI, 1/3 of revenue).

Our \(85 \text{PT}\) is derived using \(\sim 19 \text{x}\) or FY2026E EPS, which is in line with other stable LC names increasing EPS CAGR at the low- DD level. Downside risks include: 1) SIHY daily adoption/competition, 2) Broader economic headwinds, 3) MiSight competition, 4) Paragard share gains, 5) tax outlook, 6) competition. Upside risks include: 1) recessionary headwinds are significantly less severe than initially expected, 2) continued trade- ups to premium lenses, 3) Orthok and fertility proving more resilient in a difficult economic environment, and 4) overall CL share gains.
